Benefits:
• Large influence over the maps produced by the Alchemy AOE Community relative to time/work invested.
• Satisfaction of helping a scripter produce a competitive and "well-received" map for community games or (more importantly) a competition.  

Requirements:
• Be an Alchemy Affiliate.
• Must have an understanding of how Alchemy AOE "competitivity" scoring works. 
• Review random maps produced by various scripters and score them according to community standards for "competitivity". 
• May provides feedback for how maps can be revised to improve scoring. 
• Provides input on how "competitivity" scoring process may be improved.
• Must be 1500++ on the ranked AOE2DE 1v1 Ladder. 

Additional Notes:
• This is a passive role. It is awarded so that cartographers and map-organizers know who to approach when seeking counsel. Consultants are not designers -- they simply check to make sure the map offers sufficient strategic variety to be fun to play and entertaining to watch, and offer potential ideas on how to achieve this, if needed.
